{"search_data": "Central National Means cum Merit Scholarship Scheme (NMMSS) Online Application FormTable of Contents  National Means cum Merit Scholarship Scheme (NMMSS) Application FormNMMS Scholarship 2018-19 \u2013 Rate & Number of ScholarshipNMMSS Scholarship Scheme 2018-19 \u2013 Eligibility & DetailsReferencesNational Means cum Merit Scholarship Scheme (NMMSS) Application FormBelow is the complete procedure to apply online for NMMSS Scholarship 2018 for meritorious poor students:-Visit the National Scholarship Portal at scholarships.gov.inAt homepage, go to \u201cCentral Schemes\u201d section and click at \u201cDepartment of School Education & Literacy\u201d sub-section. Next hit at \u201cApply\u201d button in front of \u2018National Means cum Merit Scholarship\u2019 or directly click this linkThen National Means cum Merit Scholarship Scheme 2018 Apply Online / Login Page will appear:-National Merit Scholarship Scheme Apply OnlineThen click at \u201cNew Student ? Register Here\u201d link as shown in the above figure. Afterwards, NMMS Scheme Registration Form will appear as follows:-National Means Merit Scholarship Registration FormFill the essential details, click at the \u201cRegister\u201d button to get Username and ID on your registered Mobile Number.After candidates can \u201cLogin\u201d using the details sent on Mobile number, Verify OTP, Change Password and then click at \u201cApply\u201d link on the dashboard to fill the NMMS Scheme Online Application Form 2018 which will appear as follows:-NMMS Scholarship 2018 Application FormFill complete details and click at the \u201cSave & Continue\u201d button to complete online application process for NMMSS Scholarship Scheme 2018-19.Students of NVS, KVS, Sainik Schools and private schools cannot fill the NMMSS Scholarship Application Form. District Education Officer will forward the list to State Nodal officers who has to verify the beneficiaries and confirm the awardees of scholarship.NMMS Scholarship 2018-19 \u2013 Rate & Number of ScholarshipCentral govt. offers a total number of 1 lakh scholarships @ 6000 p.a (500 p.m) to the selected students of Class IX every year. These scholarships are continued /renewed in Class 10th to Class 12th for study in State govt. / Govt. Aided / Local Body Schools. State Bank of India (SBI) holds the responsibility to disburse this amount directly into the bank account of students through Public Financial Management System (PFMS).Each State / UT conducts State level Examination for selection of students for the award of the National Means-cum-Merit Scholarship. This includes Mental Ability Test (MAT), Scholastic Aptitude Test (SAT). Candidates must pass MAT & SAT at-least 40% marks. For reserved category, this cut off is 32% marks. Central govt. will provide 100% funds for the scheme.NMMSS Scholarship Scheme 2018-19 \u2013 Eligibility & DetailsEvery candidate must fulfill the following eligibility criteria to become eligible for National Means-cum-Merit Scholarship Scheme:-The total family income of all the candidates from all sources must not exceed Rs. 1.5 lakh per annum.All the students will get reservation on the basis of State govt. norms.All the students must have secured 55% marks or equivalent in Class 7th to appear in the NMMSS Scholarship Examination for Class 8th.For further classes i.e from class 9th to 12th, candidates must have secured at-least 55% marks in the previous final examination. (Relaxable by 5% for SC/ ST)For more detail on Eligibility Criteria, click the link \u2013 NMMSS Scholarship 2018-19 GuidelinesNote \u2013 All the students of Class 9th and 10th needs to apply under Pre-Matric scholarship category while students of class 11th and 12th need to apply under Post-Matric scholarship category. For renewal of Scholarship, click the link \u2013 Apply for PMMS Scholarship RenewalReferences\u2014 For more details, visit the official website https://scholarships.gov.in/Also Read \u2013 Pre Matric Scholarship Scheme 